    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>My dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I am most truely grieved that I should be engaged on the day you have fixed for our transient interview. It cannot be remedied.</p>
                <p>with much sincerity I devoutly recommend you &amp; <persName ref="pe0331">miss Bull</persName> to the protection of heaven. absent or present I never forget or neglect my friends.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>with truest regard I am Dear Sir,
                        <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> ever obliged &amp;
                        <lb/>faithful serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>-</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><add place="above">98</add> 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. monday night.<note type="editorial">The year '98' is inserted in a different hand. If this 
                        letter was indeed written in 1798, August is the only month in which the 13th fell on a Monday. It is unlikely that Pennant would have been within 
                        reach of Bull during August, however, and the letter may be misplaced in this year.</note></dateline>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Please to forward the hotpressed copies as usual.<note type="editorial">It is not to clear to which of his publications Pennant refers here.</note>
                        I have nothing to put in the box.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine><persName ref="pe0313">Richard Bull</persName> Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
